OL,3,CMajority of people now get their news
OL,4,Cfrom online, Ofcom research shows
OL,6,FIt follows a downward trend of TV news
OL,7,Fviewership over the years, with 79% of
OL,8,Frespondents saying it was their
OL,9,Fprimary news source in 2018 while 70%
OL,10,Fsaid the same in 2024.
OL,12,FThe top individual sources however
OL,13,Fremain Public Service Broadcasters,
OL,14,Fwith BBC and ITV taking the top two
OL,15,Fspots.
OL,17,FHowever, both broadcasters have still
OL,18,Fsuffered a decline in viewership over
OL,19,Fthe years with 43% of respondents said
OL,20,Fthey favoured BBC One in 2024, down
OL,21,Ffrom 58% in 2019.
