OL,3,CMajority of people now get their news
OL,4,Cfrom online, Ofcom research shows
OL,6,FITV1 saw a similar decline, going from
OL,7,F40% in 2019 to 30% in 2024.
OL,9,FOnline news has instead increased - up
OL,10,Ffrom 68% in 2023 to the 71% this year.
OL,12,FAmong adults who directly access news
OL,13,Fonline, the BBC website came out top
OL,14,Fat 59%, followed by Sky News (20%),
OL,15,FThe Guardian (20%) and The Daily Mail
OL,16,F(19%).
OL,18,FSocial media has also become a
OL,19,F"significant component of online news
OL,20,Fconsumption" according to the report.
